description._content: "This interesting ecclesiastical structure upon which Governor Macquarie has left his mark, possesses many points of historical interest." - Frank Walker Designed by architect Francis Greenway and built by convict Nathanial Lucas, and following his death the construction was taken over by a Mr. James Smith. The Anglican Church celebrated its first congregation at St Lukes during October 1819, and St Lukes Day on October 18th is considered the anniversary of the Church’s construction. This image is part of a collection entitled ‘Early Australian Architecture', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel. Access the collection at the following link: www.historypin.com/channels/view/id/48441/#|collections/v... Please feel free to comment on this or any of the other images in the collection.
